Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel, halve, and
thinly slice the @Carrot{1} into half moons. Mince the @Shallot{1}. Quarter the
@Zucchini{1} lengthwise then thinly slice. Roughly chop the
@Dried Apricots{1.5%oz}. Zest and halve the @Lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #ovenproof pan{} over
medium-high heat. Season the @Chicken Thighs{16%oz}(bone-in) on both sides
with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Add to the pan, skin side down, and cook
~{3-4%minutes}, until deeply golden brown. Flip to cook ~{2-3%minutes} on
the other side. Set the chicken aside—we'll finish cooking it later.

In the same pan, heat another drizzle of olive oil over medium heat. Add the
carrot and zucchini and cook, tossing, ~{6-7%minutes}, until golden
brown and tender. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

Start the paella: In the same pan, heat another drizzle of olive oil. Add the
shallot and cook, tossing, ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add the
@Bulgur Wheat{1/2%cup} and apricot and stir to coat. Add @Water{1 1/4%cups}
and the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} to the pan. Bring to a boil, then stir in
the carrots, zucchini, and lemon zest.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, transfer to a baking dish at this
> point.

Transfer: Add the chicken back to the pan, skin-side up, and transfer to the
oven for ~{7-10%minutes}. While it cooks, chop the @Parsley{1/4%oz} and cut the
lemon into wedges.

Garnish and serve: Sprinkle the bulgur paella with parsley and serve with
lemon wedges. Serve straight from the skillet and enjoy!